-- India cbank says to conduct 7-day term repo auction for 100 bln rupees
-- 
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 08:35AM EDT
-- None



Mumbai, July 17 (Reuters) - India's central bank said on Thursday it would conduct a 7-day term repo auction for 100 billion rupees ($1.66 billion) on Friday, in order to infuse liquidity into the banking system.

The reversal of the 4-day term repo will take place on July 25, the Reserve Bank of India said.